plotInformation.title: COVID-19 Symptom Co-occurrence
plotInformation.caption: This plot shows COVID-19 symptom co-occurrence among individual patients. The most prevalent symptom is fatigue. This most commonly co-occurs with anosmia (loss of smell) and cough. Only 13.7% (241 out of 1764) of patients report 4 or more symptoms.
